text: Maddy Moore (born 17 May 2000) is a Bermudian swimmer. She competed in the women's 50 metre freestyle and women's 50 metre butterfly events at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships. In both events she did not advance to compete in the semi-finals. In 2018, she competed in the girls' 50 metre backstroke event at the 2018 Summer Youth Olympics held in Buenos Aires, Argentina. She did not qualify to compete in the semi-finals. She also competed in the girls' 50 metre butterfly, girls' 50 metre freestyle and girls' 100 metre freestyle events. ==References== Category:2000 births Category:Living people Category:Bermudian female swimmers Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Female backstroke swimmers Category:Female butterfly swimmers Category:Female freestyle swimmers Category:Swimmers at the 2018 Summer Youth Olympics
